Embedding Other Presentations
To embed your own Google Slides presentation:

Get the presentation ID from your Google Slides URL:
https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/[THIS-IS-THE-ID]/edit
Create the embed URL:
https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/[YOUR-ID]/embed?start=false&loop=false&delayms=3000
Add to your .qmd file:
&lt;iframe src="YOUR-EMBED-URL"
        width="960"
        height="569"
        allowfullscreen="true"&gt;
&lt;/iframe&gt;
Ensure sharing is enabled: The presentation must be set to ‚ÄúAnyone with the link can view‚Äù



Responsive Sizing
For responsive iframe sizing, you can use CSS:
.responsive-iframe {
  position: relative;
  width: 100%;
  padding-bottom: 56.25%; /* 16:9 aspect ratio */
  height: 0;
}

.responsive-iframe iframe {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
}
Then wrap your iframe:
&lt;div class="responsive-iframe"&gt;
  &lt;iframe src="..."&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
